The Queen's granddaughter Princess Beatrice attended a Big Jubilee Lunch last week, and she adorably told an attendee that her name was Beatrice and "the Queen is my granny." Beatrice added that she was "very, very lucky" to count the Queen as her grandmother, and over the years it has certainly been clear just how much the Princess adores the monarch. Express.co.uk takes a look back at Beatrice's incredible relationship with her royal granny.